"<div>\n  <h2>Cheddar and Spinach Grilled Sandwich with Peanut Butter Tomato Spread</h2>\n  <h3>Ingredients:</h3>\n  <ul>\n    <li>4 slices of whole-wheat bread</li>\n    <li>1 cup of chopped fresh spinach</li>\n    <li>4 slices of cheddar cheese</li>\n    <li>2 tablespoons of peanut butter</li>\n    <li>1 medium-sized tomato, sliced</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h3>Instructions:</h3>\n  <ol>\n    <li>Spread peanut butter onto one side of each slice of bread.</li>\n    <li>Place a slice of cheddar cheese on two slices of bread on the opposite side of the peanut butter spread.</li>\n    <li>Evenly distribute chopped spinach over the cheese slices.</li>\n    <li>Top the spinach with sliced tomatoes.</li>\n    <li>Add another slice of cheddar cheese on top of the tomatoes and cover with the remaining slices of bread with the peanut butter side down.</li>\n    <li>Heat a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat and place the sandwich in the pan.</li>\n    <li>Cook until the cheese is melted and the bread is golden brown, about 2-3 minutes per side.</li>\n    <li>Remove from the pan, slice and serve immediately.</li>\n  </ol>\n  <h3>Nutritional Info:</h3>\n  <p>Fat: 18g</p>\n  <p>Protein: 32g</p>\n  <p>Calories: 466</p>\n  <p>Carbohydrates: 37g</p>\n</div>"